# Overview

UV should be used as the primary package and environment manager for Python projects.

Always log an issue when a deviation is necessary and you default to standard PIP.

## Commands Reference

```bash
# Create virtual environment
uv venv

# Install from requirements.txt
uv pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install a specific package
uv pip install package-name

# Freeze dependencies
uv pip freeze > requirements.txt
```
